  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/accelerate/vimage_buffer"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " structures are the basic data structures that vImage uses for working with images. They describe an image's dimensions and contain the pixel data that vImage routines operate on."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Typically, you'll initialize a source buffer from an image and initialize and allocate a destination buffer to receive the result of a vImage operation."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Initialize a Source Buffer from a Core Graphics Image",
          "anchor": "2943389"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The vImage functions that initialize a buffer's size and data require an instantiated "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/accelerate/vimage_buffer"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " structure. Typically, you declare a buffer as a variable because these functions mutate the buffer."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "You can initialize a vImage buffer from a "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/coregraphics/cgimageref"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " instance that's acquired from the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/uiimage/1624147-cgimage"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property of an image. In the following example, the image is named "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "Flowers_2.jpg"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". The "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/accelerate/vimage_buffer/3241532-init"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " function initializes a "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/accelerate/vimage_buffer"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " structure with the image data using the format discussed in "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/accelerate/creating_a_core_graphics_image_format"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "codeListing",
          "code": [
            "guard",
            "    let cgImage = UIImage(named: \"Flowers_2.jpg\")?.cgImage,",
            "    var sourceBuffer = try? vImage_Buffer(cgImage: cgImage,",
            "                                          format: format) else {",
            "                                            return nil",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "metadata": {
            "anchor": "2943390",
            "title": "Listing 1"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": []
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Initialize and Allocate a Destination Buffer",
          "anchor": "2943391"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Typically, in addition to creating a buffer to represent your source image, you create a destination buffer to receive the result of the vImage operation. In this case, you use the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/accelerate/vimage_buffer/3241533-init"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " function to initialize a buffer of a specified size and the correct memory allocation for the bit-depth of the image:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "codeListing",
          "code": [
            "guard var destinationBuffer = try? vImage_Buffer(width: Int(sourceBuffer.width),",
            "                                                 height: Int(sourceBuffer.height),",
            "                                                 bitsPerPixel: format.bitsPerPixel) else {",
            "                                                    return nil",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "metadata": {
            "anchor": "2943393",
            "title": "Listing 2"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": []
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Free the Buffer Memory",
          "anchor": "2943394"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "After you're finished with buffers that have have their own memory allocation, it's important that you free the memory allocated to them:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "codeListing",
          "code": [
            "sourceBuffer.free()",
            "destinationBuffer.free()"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "metadata": {
            "anchor": "2943395",
            "title": "Listing 3"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": []
        }
      ]
    }
